Simulation

set.seed(42);

trajectory = function(init=10,gain_max=20,p=1/2,t_max=NA) {
  t=1;
  current_gain = init
  traj = c();
  traj[1] = current_gain;
  while (current_gain!=0 & (is.na(gain_max) | current_gain<gain_max) & (is.na(t_max) | t<t_max)) {
    current_gain = current_gain + sample(x=c(-1,+1), size = 1, prob = c(p,1-p));
    t = t + 1;
    traj[t] = current_gain;
  }
  return(traj);
}
mytraj = trajectory();

Graphique

plot(mytraj);

Temps de sÃ©jour

duration = function(traj) {
  length(traj);
}
duration(mytraj);
## [1] 33

Etat final

final_gain = function(traj) {
  traj[length(traj)];
}
final_gain(mytraj);
## [1] 0

Grand nombre de trajectoire

bankrupt_proba = function(N=1000, ...) {
  count = 0;
  for(i in 1:N) {
     mytraj = trajectory(...);
     if(final_gain(mytraj)==0) { count = count + 1; }
  }
  count/N;
}

bankrupt_proba();
## [1] 0.513

Ãtude du cas fini

etudes_gain = function(N=1000, aPMin, aPMax, aNbStep, ...) {
  wStep = (aPMax - aPMin) / aNbStep;
  wP = aPMin;
  
  wBankruptProba = c(); # Les probabilitÃ© de banqueroutes
  wProbaGain = c(); # Les probabilitÃ©s
  wDuration = c(); # Les durÃ©es moyennes
  wGain = c(); # Les gains moyen
  wI = 1;
  while(wP < aPMax){
    count = 0;
    wGain_tab = c();
    wDuration_tab = c();
    for(i in 1:N) {
       mytraj = trajectory(p=wP);
       wGain_tab[i] = final_gain(mytraj);
       wDuration_tab[i] = duration(mytraj);
       if(wGain_tab[i]==0) { count = count + 1; }
    }
    
    wBankruptProba[wI] = count / N;
    wProbaGain[wI] = wP;
    wDuration[wI] = sum(wDuration_tab) / N;
    wGain[wI] = sum(wGain_tab) / N;
  
    
    wP = wP + wStep;
    wI = wI + 1;
  }
  
  plot(wProbaGain, wBankruptProba, main="ProbabilitÃ© de banqueroute en fonction de la probabilitÃ© de perte", xlab="ProbabilitÃ© de perte au jeu", ylab="ProbabilitÃ© de banqueroute");
  plot(wProbaGain, main="DurÃ©e moyenne d'une partie en fonction de la probabilitÃ© de perte", wDuration, xlab="ProbabilitÃ© de perte au jeu", ylab="DurÃ©e moyenne");
  plot(wProbaGain, main="Gain moyen d'une partie en fonction de la probabilitÃ© de perte", wGain, xlab="ProbabilitÃ© de perte au jeu", ylab="Gains moyen");
}
etudes_gain(aN = 1000, aPMin = 0, aPMax=1, aNbStep=100)
